      Most of the friction around high-protein breakfasts comes down to one thing: eggs take time to cook in the morning. The fix is simple and takes 12 minutes once a week.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Batch hard-boil a dozen eggs every Sunday.</strong> Refrigerated in the shell, they keep for up to a week. With a dozen eggs on hand, five of the seven breakfasts above require zero morning cooking. The 60-second shake-and-eggs option becomes genuinely 60 seconds. The yogurt option is grab-and-go.
    </p>

